2
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:37,900
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:39,310 --> 00:01:42,250
[Autumn, 1980]

4
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:12,990
Is there anyone?

5
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:18,020
[Home]

6
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:22,710
Grandpa.

7
00:02:23,030 --> 00:02:24,829
These knee pads are warm, right?

8
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:26,050
Yes, they're warm.

9
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:27,190
Very warm.

10
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:28,030
They are made of pure cotton,

11
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:30,490
specially designed to help with arthritis.

12
00:02:30,990 --> 00:02:32,790
All thanks to both of you.

13
00:02:34,270 --> 00:02:34,990
Dawa,

14
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:37,630
since I'm still able to walk,

15
00:02:38,350 --> 00:02:40,390
you should get married and have a baby soon.

16
00:02:40,390 --> 00:02:42,590
I'll help you with babysitting then.

17
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:45,110
Isn't it great? You don't have to worry about it.

18
00:02:45,110 --> 00:02:46,110
I can help you too.

19
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:47,460
What can you do?

20
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:49,310
You're still a kid.

21
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:50,450
How can you help me?

22
00:02:51,270 --> 00:02:51,870
Grandpa.

23
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,180
Besides,

24
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:54,550
this matter can't be rushed.

25
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:56,280
I can't believe you're not in a hurry.

26
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,790
There are hundreds of girls

27
00:02:57,790 --> 00:02:58,829
in the factory.

28
00:02:59,390 --> 00:03:00,950
Is none of them suitable?

29
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,120
Our supervisor

30
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,280
wants to introduce his daughter to me.

31
00:03:05,210 --> 00:03:06,490
What is a supervisor?

32
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:08,310
The supervisor of the construction project.

33
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:09,330
He manages all of us

34
00:03:09,330 --> 00:03:10,530
and has a lot of power.

35
00:03:11,090 --> 00:03:12,350
You should go meet her.

36
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,160
We're not social climbers.

37
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:14,950
We don't care

38
00:03:14,950 --> 00:03:16,270
whether he is a supervisor or not.

39
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:17,390
As long as you two get along well,

40
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:18,750
it's a good marriage.

41
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:19,990
I did meet her.

42
00:03:20,430 --> 00:03:21,430
She's quite nice.

43
00:03:21,620 --> 00:03:23,810
But she has a bad temper

44
00:03:23,970 --> 00:03:25,300
and is very aggressive.

45
00:03:27,270 --> 00:03:28,230
Now he picks on her.

46
00:03:28,230 --> 00:03:29,829
You see, he's picking on her.

47
00:03:30,630 --> 00:03:32,350
Our family is not bad now.

48
00:03:32,790 --> 00:03:33,829
Xiaowa will be

49
00:03:33,829 --> 00:03:34,920
a college student soon.

50
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,200
He can go to my place.

51
00:03:36,430 --> 00:03:37,590
I'll take you there too.

52
00:03:37,590 --> 00:03:39,390
We can live a good life together.

53
00:03:39,670 --> 00:03:40,310
Okay.

54
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,850
You two focus on developing your relationship.

55
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:46,870
When the time comes, I'll help you

56
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:48,400
take care of your children.

57
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:50,760
Then I'll come back.

58
00:03:51,710 --> 00:03:53,710
I can't leave this place.

59
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:56,870
I'm used to it.

60
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:03,150
Put her down.

61
00:04:03,190 --> 00:04:05,350
Let her rest.

62
00:04:05,670 --> 00:04:07,800
You keep carrying her and rubbing her.

63
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,510
Can she stand it?

64
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:11,360
This little kid is very clever.

65
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:12,180
She can tell

66
00:04:12,180 --> 00:04:13,310
who a good person is.

67
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:14,830
Why didn't she let you carry her?

68
00:04:14,830 --> 00:04:16,000
She is onto you.

69
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,420
-She is onto you.
-Come on.

70
00:04:17,420 --> 00:04:19,390
Let Grandpa carry you.

71
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:20,310
See if she'll come.

72
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:21,630
-Come here.
-Let's see if she'll go to you.

73
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:22,450
-Come here.
-Let's see if she'll go to you.

74
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:23,980
Grandma, Grandpa, stop fighting.

75
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:24,860
Time to eat.

76
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:27,550
Zi.

77
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:29,390
Let her eat first.

78
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:31,430
Yeah, eat first.

79
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:33,870
She likes me. How adorable she is.

80
00:04:34,030 --> 00:04:35,120
Listen.

81
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,920
Don't worry about Zi's illness.

82
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:38,270
I know a TCM physician.

83
00:04:38,270 --> 00:04:40,390
If treated according to traditional Chinese medicine methods, it can be cured.

84
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:41,150
Or else,

85
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:42,390
I know a priest.

86
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,250
-Wait, Mom.
-A priest.

87
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,070
Well, I've already arranged for someone

88
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,520
to treat Zi.

89
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:50,150
Currently, it looks very effective.

90
00:04:50,710 --> 00:04:51,390
Well...

91
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:53,390
What?

92
00:04:54,710 --> 00:04:55,670
What are you talking about?

93
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:57,070
What did I say? I was watching TV.

94
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:58,190
You were gesturing.

95
00:04:58,190 --> 00:04:59,520
-I didn't.
-Don't talk.

96
00:04:59,909 --> 00:05:00,550
Go ahead.

97
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,270
I'm afraid your treatment method

98
00:05:02,270 --> 00:05:03,750
might conflict

99
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:05,070
with ours

100
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:06,290
and cause issues later.

101
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:06,970
Let's see

102
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,310
how effective this treatment is.

103
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:10,630
If it doesn't work well on my end,

104
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:14,130
I'll definitely ask you to help find someone in the future.

105
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,070
You're right. Okay.

106
00:05:17,070 --> 00:05:18,870
Go ahead and do your thing first.

107
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:22,390
Where is Baoyu?

108
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:24,920
Why isn't he home during the Chinese New Year?

109
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:27,220
Grandma, you don't know.

110
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:27,910
The Chinese New Year

111
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:30,390
is the best time for Baoyu to pursue love.

112
00:05:30,750 --> 00:05:31,610
Where did he go?

113
00:05:31,970 --> 00:05:34,490
He went to my...

114
00:05:34,909 --> 00:05:35,850
Your teacher's house?

115
00:05:35,850 --> 00:05:36,890
No.

116
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,880
Where did he go?

117
00:05:39,370 --> 00:05:40,630
The director's place.

118
00:05:40,909 --> 00:05:41,990
He made a big step forward

119
00:05:41,990 --> 00:05:43,390
in life.

120
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:45,110
Our son

121
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:46,120
didn't win over the teacher,

122
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,600
and now he's shamelessly going after the director.

123
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,950
You taught him well.

124
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:49,990
Come on.

125
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:51,800
Look who's here.

126
00:05:52,950 --> 00:05:54,550
Director Xiao, you're here.

127
00:05:54,710 --> 00:05:56,230
Hello.

128
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,150
Happy Chinese New Year.

129
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:59,470
-Happy Chinese New Year.
-Happy Chinese New Year.

130
00:05:59,470 --> 00:06:00,590
-What's wrong with you?
-What happened to you?

131
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:01,790
I'm fine.

132
00:06:01,790 --> 00:06:02,670
He fell when helping me

133
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:03,830
hang up the spring couplets.

134
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:04,830
Are you stupid?

135
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:05,790
Is your bone okay?

136
00:06:05,790 --> 00:06:06,950
I'm fine, Pengfei.

137
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:07,830
Apply some ice on it.

138
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:08,750
No need.

139
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:09,930
Come on, Director Xiao.

140
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:11,030
Let me change my shoes.

141
00:06:11,030 --> 00:06:12,750
No need. Come on in.

142
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:13,630
Come on in.

143
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:14,830
I'll get you some ice.

144
00:06:14,990 --> 00:06:15,910
Hello, Director.

145
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:17,030
Hello, Director.

146
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:19,360
This is not a home visit. Why do you bow?

147
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:22,830
Look at these kids.

148
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:24,870
Director Xiao really has authority.

149
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:27,070
They immediately behaved themselves.

150
00:06:27,670 --> 00:06:29,470
Mom, this is Director Xiao

151
00:06:29,470 --> 00:06:31,030
from the school, right?

152
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:32,770
Hello, Director Xiao.

153
00:06:33,350 --> 00:06:34,310
Director Xiao.

154
00:06:34,330 --> 00:06:35,710
I'm so happy that you're here.

155
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:36,550
Let me do it.

156
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,880
You're more beautiful

157
00:06:38,909 --> 00:06:39,710
than I heard.

158
00:06:40,990 --> 00:06:41,950
Aunt...

159
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:43,070
My mom.

160
00:06:43,260 --> 00:06:44,270
Baoshan told me

161
00:06:44,290 --> 00:06:44,890
that

162
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,530
Aunt and Uncle are here for the Chinese New Year.

163
00:06:46,530 --> 00:06:48,030
Happy Chinese New Year, Uncle.

164
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:49,110
I came in a hurry today

165
00:06:49,110 --> 00:06:50,070
so I didn't prepare anything.

166
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:50,950
Sorry.

167
00:06:52,790 --> 00:06:53,710
Let me tell you.

168
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:55,110
No need to prepare anything.

169
00:06:55,110 --> 00:06:56,350
Everyone here is one of us.

170
00:06:56,350 --> 00:06:57,510
There's nothing to prepare.

171
00:06:57,510 --> 00:06:58,690
Make yourself at home.

172
00:06:58,690 --> 00:07:00,410
We're lucky to have you here.

173
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,390
Say something.

174
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,650
Hello, Director Xiao.

175
00:07:07,110 --> 00:07:07,670
Uncle.

176
00:07:07,690 --> 00:07:09,250
Just call me Xiao Fang.

177
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:11,310
I'm flattered.

178
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:12,950
Listen, Director.

179
00:07:12,950 --> 00:07:14,590
You've helped Baoyu

180
00:07:14,590 --> 00:07:15,820
a lot.

181
00:07:15,820 --> 00:07:16,480
So we are very happy

182
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,670
that you came.

183
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:19,310
Mom, I'm Jia Baoshan, what Baoyu?

184
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:19,630
Is that a name

185
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:20,910
for a true man?

186
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:22,240
You forgot your origin.

187
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:24,170
The name given by your parents

188
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:25,390
is Jia Baoyu.

189
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:26,630
You should take it to the grave.

190
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:27,270
That name, Jia Baoyu,

191
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:28,630
was given by Cao Xueqin.

192
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:29,920
What does that have to do with you?

193
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:30,470
Mom, look at you.

194
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:31,600
Can't you read?

195
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:31,860
Your knowledge

196
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:33,030
of Dream of the Red Chamber

197
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:34,310
has really become a part of you.

198
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:35,430
Look at you.

199
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:36,350
See?

200
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,510
-Don't just stand here.
-Come.

201
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:38,310
Have a seat.

202
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:39,330
-Okay.
-Right.

203
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:43,550
Open your mouth.

204
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,430
Drink it.

205
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:50,550
What is this?

206
00:07:50,650 --> 00:07:52,510
I'm afraid you'll drink at night.

207
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:54,230
Finish it.

208
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:57,530
I'm on duty. I won't drink.

209
00:08:00,230 --> 00:08:02,110
It's good for your stomach.

210
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:03,670
It's the Chinese New Year.

211
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:05,070
Yet you drugged me.

212
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:06,630
Look at you.

213
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:08,030
Why do you have to be on duty

214
00:08:08,030 --> 00:08:09,310
every New Year's Eve?

215
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:11,190
Then who should I assign to be on duty?

216
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:12,490
Then why does the factory manager

217
00:08:12,490 --> 00:08:14,150
never take a duty shift every year?

218
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:15,150
You think you are so capable.

219
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:15,990
It's because I'm not the factory manager.

220
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:17,480
If you make me the factory manager, just wait and see.

221
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,790
I'll take a shift on New Year's Eve

222
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:19,910
and set an example.

223
00:08:19,970 --> 00:08:21,150
What's going on, Dad?

224
00:08:21,150 --> 00:08:23,350
Are you going to be the factory manager?

225
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:24,630
Can I

226
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:25,390
smoothly take over

227
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,590
and become the director?

228
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:27,670
First, you can smoothly get lost.

229
00:08:27,670 --> 00:08:28,630
Go over there.

230
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:30,750
Come here.

231
00:08:31,350 --> 00:08:33,390
Why did you kick him?

232
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:37,100
Take it off.

233
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:39,640
Am I not wearing it anymore?

234
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:41,049
It's a new year.

235
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:43,350
We have to switch to a new one.

236
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,050
Last year was quite good.

237
00:08:45,050 --> 00:08:46,080
I'll keep you safe.

238
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,760
This one is fine too.

239
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:51,240
May it keep our Li Si

240
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,430
safe and sound this year as well.

241
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:55,050
No, you tied me up again.

242
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,080
I'll take the old one.

243
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,280
Wait.

244
00:08:59,470 --> 00:09:01,560
Is this all we're eating for the New Year?

245
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,310
Your dad still has to

246
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:03,240
go on duty later.

247
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:05,070
There are still customers at the restaurant.

248
00:09:05,070 --> 00:09:07,000
Hurry up and eat while there's time.

249
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,230
Seriously, who does this?

250
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:09,580
Running off on New Year's Eve?

251
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:11,010
This is our New Year's Eve dinner!

252
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:12,370
What's so special about New Year's Eve dinner?

253
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:13,670
Have we treated you poorly

254
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:14,190
usually?

255
00:09:14,190 --> 00:09:14,870
Regular meals are different from

256
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:16,310
New Year's Eve dinner.

257
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:19,270
We'll have fewer chances to have a New Year's Eve dinner.

258
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:19,950
Why can't you

259
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:20,550
talk properly

260
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:21,550
with your mouth?

261
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:27,280
I'm getting frustrated with both of you during the New Year.

262
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:28,880
Go help out at

263
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:30,070
your mom's restaurant later.

264
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,400
If you don't go, I'll deal with you myself.

265
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:36,490
I want to eat pork knuckles.

266
00:09:36,490 --> 00:09:38,820
You look like a big pork knuckle yourself.

267
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:40,960
Can you stop shouting?

268
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,410
Son, be good.

269
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,980
Eat the dumpling first.

270
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:44,750
It's mutton stuffing.

271
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,590
I made it specially for you.

272
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:46,510
I'll make a call in a bit

273
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:47,230
and have them deliver it.

274
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:48,600
You're spoiling him.

275
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,450
Bring me a bottle of liquor too.

276
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:53,070
Didn't you say you weren't drinking today?

277
00:09:53,070 --> 00:09:53,770
I've taken the medicine.

278
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:55,970
Wouldn't drinking protect my stomach?

279
00:09:56,540 --> 00:09:57,510
Just spoil him.

280
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,880
He doesn't look like me.

281
00:09:59,910 --> 00:10:01,110
Eat your food.

282
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,510
Why are you so talkative?

283
00:10:02,530 --> 00:10:03,730
Come on. Have one too.

284
00:10:03,950 --> 00:10:04,790
Mom, how much lucky money

285
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:06,110
are you giving to me this year?

286
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,070
How old are you?

287
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:07,990
Why do you still want money?

288
00:10:07,990 --> 00:10:09,870
No, you should still give me what I'm supposed to get.

289
00:10:09,870 --> 00:10:11,190
No way, there's none for you.

290
00:10:11,190 --> 00:10:12,520
Then how much are you giving to my brother?

291
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,980
It's rare for him to come back.

292
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:14,830
He's so grown up,

293
00:10:14,830 --> 00:10:16,630
what does he need lucky money for?

294
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:17,390
See.

295
00:10:17,430 --> 00:10:18,240
Aunt Yue.

296
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:21,290
This past year, my dad has been busy with work,

297
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,910
and he's not the type to say sweet things.

298
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:24,070
You've been the one

299
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:25,620
taking care of everything.

300
00:10:25,650 --> 00:10:28,040
You must have suffered a lot.

301
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:28,680
Here.

302
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:30,920
Let me toast you first.

303
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:33,680
Why are you being so formal all of a sudden?

304
00:10:34,350 --> 00:10:35,160
Come on.

305
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:36,990
I never have a hard time.

306
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:38,120
Everything's fine.

307
00:10:38,570 --> 00:10:39,180
Here.

308
00:10:40,990 --> 00:10:42,070
Drink slowly.

309
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:43,750
Don't drink too much.

310
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,150
Have some more food.

311
00:10:45,150 --> 00:10:46,550
Have some more food, Tao.

312
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:48,630
The dumplings are so delicious.

313
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:49,350
-Right?
-I think so too.

314
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:50,460
Is it because Tao is back?

315
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:51,510
Of course.

316
00:10:51,510 --> 00:10:53,430
It's specially made for Tao.

317
00:10:53,730 --> 00:10:54,800
Here, Dad.

318
00:10:54,830 --> 00:10:55,690
You're biased.

319
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:57,390
Don't toast me. Just eat.

320
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:58,330
-Dad, it's rare for me
-Hurry up and eat.

321
00:10:58,330 --> 00:10:59,420
to come back.

322
00:11:00,020 --> 00:11:01,660
Fine. Come on.

323
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:05,030
Dad, don't always focus so much on work.

324
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,340
Put more effort into the family.

325
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,780
The home is your real battlefield.

326
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:11,980
Yes, come on.

327
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:16,000
Take it easy.

328
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:21,430
Although Min

329
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,670
is no longer a child,

330
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:25,150
she's still the youngest in our family.

331
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:27,230
From now on, she will be

332
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,630
the focus of our protection.

333
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:29,760
When I'm not at home,

334
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:30,950
you two must make sure that

335
00:11:30,950 --> 00:11:32,550
Min isn't treated unfairly.

336
00:11:32,790 --> 00:11:33,590
Do you hear me?

337
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:35,670
Is it true that our brother is always worried about you,

338
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:38,000
afraid that we won't take good care of you?

339
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:39,180
With my brother backing me up,

340
00:11:39,180 --> 00:11:40,510
my status in the family is quite high.

341
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:40,990
Here, Brother.

342
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:42,070
-I toast you.
-It's quite high.

343
00:11:42,070 --> 00:11:42,670
Come on.

344
00:11:43,910 --> 00:11:45,240
Today is really joyful.

345
00:11:45,930 --> 00:11:46,590
So happy.

346
00:11:46,590 --> 00:11:47,870
Mom, let me pour you some liquor.

347
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:49,430
Come on, let's pour the drinks ourselves.

348
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:49,990
Mom.

349
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:50,570
All right.

350
00:11:50,570 --> 00:11:52,410
Come on, Dad.

351
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:54,750
Here, honey.

352
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:55,910
Come on.

353
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,150
Why don't you have a drink too?

354
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:57,990
Director Xiao, have some.

355
00:11:57,990 --> 00:11:59,030
No, thanks.

356
00:11:59,030 --> 00:12:00,230
She can drink.

357
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,780
Drink some if you can drink.

358
00:12:01,990 --> 00:12:03,080
Pour her a little.

359
00:12:03,470 --> 00:12:04,830
I want to thank my wife.

360
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:05,820
Here you go.

361
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:07,310
Thank you.

362
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:09,510
Alright, let me say a few words.

363
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:10,010
Okay.

364
00:12:10,510 --> 00:12:12,150
The country has its laws, and the family has its rules.

365
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,030
You can tell

366
00:12:13,050 --> 00:12:13,950
how well a household is managed

367
00:12:13,950 --> 00:12:15,590
by looking at the one in charge.

368
00:12:15,590 --> 00:12:16,850
As the old saying goes,

369
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:18,630
'May there be wealth and abundance, year after year.'

370
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:19,690
Guests come first.

371
00:12:20,060 --> 00:12:22,130
Today, I want to present the first fish

372
00:12:22,130 --> 00:12:23,930
to our most honored guest.

373
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:24,900
Fang.

374
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:26,270
Here.

375
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:26,830
Fang.

376
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:28,190
Thank you, Aunt.

377
00:12:28,190 --> 00:12:29,750
Spring silkworms spin till death, running out of yearning thread;

378
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,990
Burning "candies" weep, till no more tears.

379
00:12:31,990 --> 00:12:32,630
Grandma,

380
00:12:32,870 --> 00:12:34,350
it's "candles".

381
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:35,830
What? They're almost the same.

382
00:12:35,830 --> 00:12:36,820
The candles.

383
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,710
Yes, they're the same.

384
00:12:38,710 --> 00:12:40,110
Both mean the same thing.

385
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:41,710
That's good then.

386
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:42,790
Here's the second one.

387
00:12:42,790 --> 00:12:44,190
I'll give Shanqing,

388
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:45,750
the great scientist.

389
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:46,950
Even Beethoven said,

390
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:49,080
"Through suffering, we move toward joy."

391
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,350
-Thank you, Grandma.
-Grandma.

392
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:52,150
Beethoven was a pianist.

393
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:53,580
He could play the piano?

394
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,350
Alright, now

395
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:56,710
I'm giving it to my son-in-law.

396
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:58,060
When he's outside,

397
00:12:58,190 --> 00:13:00,230
he saves lives. How noble it is.

398
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,410
At home,

399
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,230
he shows unity, mutual assistance, and dedication.

400
00:13:03,230 --> 00:13:05,350
Thank you, Mom, your summary

401
00:13:05,350 --> 00:13:06,630
is very accurate.

402
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:08,030
Now I feel a bit embarrassed.

403
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,030
Don't flatter me.

404
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:11,150
Guess who I'm giving this fish to.

405
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,170
I give it to my daughter.

406
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:14,220
Yu,

407
00:13:14,910 --> 00:13:16,790
only a mother knows

408
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:19,070
the pain and happiness of being a mother.

409
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:19,800
Understand?

410
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:21,590
Thank you, Mom. Thank you.

411
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:23,430
Here, this one

412
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:24,600
is for Miaomiao.

413
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:25,590
Thank you, Grandma.

414
00:13:25,590 --> 00:13:27,310
Miaomiao, Yaya, come on.

415
00:13:27,310 --> 00:13:28,270
One for each of you.

416
00:13:28,270 --> 00:13:29,400
Thank you, Grandma.

417
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:30,590
Take it.

418
00:13:30,590 --> 00:13:32,350
Take good care of your parents.

419
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:32,910
Got it?

420
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:33,840
-Yes.
-Thank you, Grandma.

421
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:34,750
Okay.

422
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:36,030
Let's have a drink.

423
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:39,270
What should Baoshan and I eat?

424
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,750
Didn't I tell you just now?

425
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,430
The country has its laws, and the family has its rules.

426
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:43,720
There are rewards and punishments.

427
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,310
Think about last year,

428
00:13:45,330 --> 00:13:46,870
what contributions did you make to this family?

429
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:47,750
What have you done?

430
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,630
Just eating a couple of green onions

431
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:49,670
-is pretty good, isn't it?
-No, Mom.

432
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:51,040
-Last year, I...
-Shut up.

433
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:51,670
Objection!

434
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:52,430
Overrule.

435
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,130
Come on.

436
00:13:54,190 --> 00:13:55,030
Let's eat.

437
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:56,390
Happy Chinese New Year, everyone.

438
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:56,910
Happy Chinese New Year.

439
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:58,640
Wishing everyone good health!

440
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,030
Coming.

441
00:14:26,710 --> 00:14:27,710
-Xiaowa.
-Happy Chinese New Year, Aunt.

442
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:28,870
Happy Chinese New Year.

443
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:29,670
Come on in.

444
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:31,030
No, thanks.

445
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:31,750
This is the New Year's goods

446
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:32,790
we prepared ourselves.

447
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,820
My grandpa sent me to pay a New Year's visit.

448
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:36,010
So many?

449
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,830
Please convey my gratitude to your grandpa.

450
00:14:37,830 --> 00:14:38,500
We've enjoyed a lot of your family's fish

451
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,050
in the past year.

452
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:43,470
Mom, my grandma is calling you.

453
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:45,120
Go now.

454
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:46,120
Thank you.

455
00:14:47,750 --> 00:14:49,280
Why don't you come in?

456
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:51,510
I'm going to pay a New Year's visit to the principal.

457
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:52,870
So I'm going in.

458
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:55,120
What is this?

459
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:56,420
Dumplings with wild vegetable stuffing.

460
00:14:56,420 --> 00:14:57,730
I made the wrappers myself.

461
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:58,790
I don't know if you can

462
00:14:58,790 --> 00:14:59,710
get used to it.

463
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:01,430
I love wild vegetable dumplings.

464
00:15:01,430 --> 00:15:02,890
My grandma loves them too.

465
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:03,950
That's good.

466
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:05,090
This is for you.

467
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:09,040
Happy Chinese New Year.

468
00:15:09,790 --> 00:15:10,430
Xiaowa.

469
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,780
-Xiaowa is here too.
-Happy Chinese New Year.

470
00:15:12,780 --> 00:15:14,350
Li Si, moving so many things,

471
00:15:14,350 --> 00:15:15,870
have you emptied out your whole house?

472
00:15:15,870 --> 00:15:17,190
Isn't Grandma and Grandpa here?

473
00:15:17,190 --> 00:15:18,390
I have to behave well.

474
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:19,910
I'm leaving.

475
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:21,510
You're leaving?

476
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,280
My brother is back.

477
00:15:25,310 --> 00:15:26,570
We'll go play with you later.

478
00:15:26,570 --> 00:15:27,330
Okay.

479
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:28,850
Bye.

480
00:15:29,350 --> 00:15:30,550
I'll go to your home to pay a New Year's visit later.

481
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:31,310
Bye, Xiaowa.

482
00:15:31,310 --> 00:15:32,070
Bye.

483
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:34,960
What did Xiaowa bring?

484
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:36,190
Wild vegetable dumplings.

485
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:37,140
He made them myself.

486
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:38,710
Look, they smell so good.

487
00:15:38,730 --> 00:15:39,730
Yaya, listen.

488
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,150
Wild vegetable dumplings.

489
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:43,030
Those are things that recall the sorrows of the past and savor the joys of the present.

490
00:15:43,030 --> 00:15:43,670
Try one.

491
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,590
My grandma hasn't eaten yet.

492
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:48,270
Happy Chinese New Year, Grandma and Grandpa.

493
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:49,270
Hello, Grandma, Grandpa, Uncle.

494
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:50,230
Hello, Aunt. Happy Chinese New Year.

495
00:15:50,230 --> 00:15:51,310
Li Si is here.

496
00:15:51,330 --> 00:15:52,850
Come here. Take a seat.

497
00:15:53,710 --> 00:15:54,640
You're all here.

498
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:56,910
Oh yeah.

499
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:57,830
Here.

500
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,560
I brought this

501
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:00,440
wild ginseng from the Changbai Mountain

502
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:02,160
for you two.

503
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:02,900
My mom wanted to

504
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:03,790
give it to my grandma, but I didn't let her.

505
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:05,520
I brought it to you two instead.

506
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:08,430
My grandson-in-law is so generous.

507
00:16:08,430 --> 00:16:08,990
Grandma.

508
00:16:08,990 --> 00:16:10,990
You'll make a fortune in the future.

509
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:12,070
What grandson-in-law?

510
00:16:12,070 --> 00:16:13,110
Grandma, try it.

511
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:15,230
They're wild vegetable dumplings, given by Xiaowa.

512
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:15,950
Great.

513
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:16,900
Grandma,

514
00:16:17,190 --> 00:16:18,070
I'll treat you well in the future.

515
00:16:18,070 --> 00:16:19,590
Tell me what you want to eat.

516
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:20,710
If you like wild vegetable dumplings,

517
00:16:20,710 --> 00:16:21,570
I have some too.

518
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:23,110
Not only does it fill you up, but it's also delicious.

519
00:16:23,110 --> 00:16:24,120
Good.

520
00:16:24,340 --> 00:16:25,500
That's great.

521
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:27,350
You know what?

522
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:27,990
Since the older generation has already

523
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:28,950
made their decisions,

524
00:16:28,950 --> 00:16:29,970
as the younger generation,

525
00:16:29,970 --> 00:16:31,770
we shouldn't keep pushing back.

526
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:33,770
By the way, look.

527
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:35,230
I knew Yuan Shanqing

528
00:16:35,230 --> 00:16:35,970
and Zi were here.

529
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:36,570
Look.

530
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:38,390
I brought Zi a little doll.

531
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:40,120
-That's great.
-Do you like it?

532
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:41,700
-That's great.
-Thank you, Si.

533
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,360
No worries. As long as Zi likes it.

534
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,470
How nice he is.

535
00:16:44,470 --> 00:16:44,950
Grandpa.

536
00:16:44,950 --> 00:16:46,310
-He's thoughtful.
-How's your health?

537
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:47,230
Not bad.

538
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:50,500
Your grandma didn't piss me off to that extent.

539
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:51,570
Don't believe him.

540
00:16:51,570 --> 00:16:52,650
He's just nagging.

541
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:54,150
When did I piss you off?

542
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:54,630
Brother.

543
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:55,630
Happy Chinese New Year, Miaomiao.

544
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:57,830
Come on in.

545
00:16:58,630 --> 00:17:00,030
Brother's here.

546
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:01,190
My brother is more handsome now.

547
00:17:01,190 --> 00:17:02,790
Anyway, he's from a big city.

548
00:17:03,070 --> 00:17:03,870
Have a seat.

549
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:05,069
Why bother buying things? It's just wasting money.

550
00:17:05,069 --> 00:17:06,589
Look at these things.

551
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:07,869
Really.

552
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:08,740
Grandpa, Grandma.

553
00:17:08,740 --> 00:17:09,640
This is the egg waffle I queued up to buy for you

554
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,710
from the most famous pastry shop

555
00:17:10,710 --> 00:17:12,230
in Shenzhen.

556
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:13,730
Really?

557
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:15,960
This is great.

558
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:17,880
It's a pity if

559
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:18,829
Si doesn't go on to be a leader after this.

560
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:20,760
He will at least be a section chief.

561
00:17:21,619 --> 00:17:23,190
Did you change your shampoo?

562
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:24,030
No.

563
00:17:24,569 --> 00:17:26,230
My brother bought me perfume.

564
00:17:26,890 --> 00:17:27,770
It smells good.

565
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,860
It smells different from that rouge.

566
00:17:29,860 --> 00:17:31,260
He bought it in Hong Kong.

567
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:32,430
Your brother is so nice.

568
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:34,030
He even went to Hong Kong to buy it for you.

569
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:35,030
Who knows?

570
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:36,380
What do you think? I'll listen to you.

571
00:17:36,380 --> 00:17:37,550
It's specially for you.

572
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:38,200
Let me see.

573
00:17:40,190 --> 00:17:40,930
Do you like it?

