00:35:08,310 --> 00:35:09,910
and left her to face it alone.

1146
00:35:10,490 --> 00:35:11,610
I was young before.

1147
00:35:12,310 --> 00:35:12,850
I didn't know

1148
00:35:12,850 --> 00:35:14,250
how to face these things.

1149
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:15,950
After I went to college

1150
00:35:15,950 --> 00:35:17,710
and went to another city,

1151
00:35:18,620 --> 00:35:20,150
I realized what freedom is.

1152
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:24,320
One year during the summer vacation of my sophomore year,

1153
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,920
I took a train to Guangzhou with my classmates.

1154
00:35:26,990 --> 00:35:28,710
Next to us was a little boy

1155
00:35:29,030 --> 00:35:30,270
with his mom and dad.

1156
00:35:30,750 --> 00:35:32,390
His mom, being careless,

1157
00:35:32,410 --> 00:35:34,270
left the luggage on the platform,

1158
00:35:34,430 --> 00:35:35,750
but the train left,

1159
00:35:35,770 --> 00:35:37,500
and they couldn't retrieve it.

1160
00:35:37,860 --> 00:35:39,100
His dad said,

1161
00:35:39,390 --> 00:35:41,070
"Your mom is such a silly goose."

1162
00:35:41,070 --> 00:35:42,880
His mom kept laughing and said,

1163
00:35:43,990 --> 00:35:46,450
"Looks like I've got early-onset Alzheimer's!"

1164
00:35:46,450 --> 00:35:48,170
Then the boy said,

1165
00:35:48,500 --> 00:35:49,720
"Luckily, I'm not like you two.

1166
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:50,850
I have a good memory.

1167
00:35:50,870 --> 00:35:52,400
My backpack is still here!"

1168
00:35:53,090 --> 00:35:55,420
And the three of them burst into laughter.

1169
00:35:56,070 --> 00:35:57,660
I was sitting next to them

1170
00:35:58,390 --> 00:36:00,120
and suddenly felt like crying.

1171
00:36:01,150 --> 00:36:02,310
In that moment,

1172
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:03,950
I really envied

1173
00:36:03,950 --> 00:36:05,210
their family of three.

1174
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:07,150
I was thinking,

1175
00:36:07,250 --> 00:36:09,580
that if something like this happened in my family,

1176
00:36:09,580 --> 00:36:12,310
we would have definitely been in a huge argument.

1177
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:14,360
That day, I realized

1178
00:36:15,110 --> 00:36:16,440
that there can be such a lighthearted,

1179
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:17,970
joyful family atmosphere.

1180
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:19,820
I realized that a harmonious attitude

1181
00:36:19,820 --> 00:36:21,030
between parents

1182
00:36:21,030 --> 00:36:21,870
can help a child

1183
00:36:21,870 --> 00:36:22,750
face difficulties

1184
00:36:22,750 --> 00:36:23,870
without fear.

1185
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:27,340
From that moment on, I told myself

1186
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:29,350
that I didn't want to be influenced

1187
00:36:29,350 --> 00:36:31,080
by the tension, indifference,

1188
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:33,080
and conflicts in my family anymore.

1189
00:36:33,750 --> 00:36:34,430
I want to be a

1190
00:36:34,430 --> 00:36:35,830
lighthearted and happy person.

1191
00:36:35,830 --> 00:36:37,170
I don't want to live cautiously,

1192
00:36:37,170 --> 00:36:38,090
being sensitive and suspicious

1193
00:36:38,090 --> 00:36:39,010
like before.

1194
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:42,260
I wanted to break free from here.

1195
00:36:52,660 --> 00:36:53,310
Aunt Yue.

1196
00:36:55,030 --> 00:36:55,550
Over the years,

1197
00:36:55,550 --> 00:36:57,280
you've worked hard to raise me,

1198
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:00,360
and I remember

1199
00:37:02,150 --> 00:37:04,280
how much you've cared for this family.

1200
00:37:05,550 --> 00:37:06,720
We are one family,

1201
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:08,350
and it's natural for families to have

1202
00:37:08,350 --> 00:37:09,880
their ups and downs, right?

1203
00:37:10,310 --> 00:37:11,390
But living life

1204
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:13,700
is not about competing with each other.

1205
00:37:14,310 --> 00:37:16,620
Whether we have blood ties or not isn't important.

1206
00:37:16,620 --> 00:37:17,670
How others view our family

1207
00:37:17,670 --> 00:37:18,930
is also not important.

1208
00:37:19,210 --> 00:37:20,340
What matters is that

1209
00:37:20,810 --> 00:37:22,560
we are only responsible for ourselves

1210
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:24,170
and for our family.

1211
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:26,970
We only live for a few decades,

1212
00:37:28,710 --> 00:37:30,370
and it's just this one family.

1213
00:37:34,390 --> 00:37:35,390
I'm sorry.

1214
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:38,880
It's my fault.

1215
00:37:44,990 --> 00:37:46,190
Okay, no more crying.

1216
00:37:47,890 --> 00:37:50,170
I'm sorry, it's my fault.

1217
00:37:50,590 --> 00:37:52,520
You've done really well, Aunt Yue.

1218
00:37:52,930 --> 00:37:54,890
You've truly put in a lot of effort

1219
00:37:55,260 --> 00:37:57,590
taking care of Dad and Min all these years.

1220
00:37:57,860 --> 00:37:59,390
You've really worked hard.

1221
00:38:06,360 --> 00:38:08,470
Alright, alright, no more crying.

1222
00:38:14,190 --> 00:38:16,140
Do you know how many years it's been

1223
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:19,270
since my mom made this vest?

1224
00:38:20,580 --> 00:38:22,380
It's as old-fashioned as can be.

1225
00:38:24,190 --> 00:38:26,310
But I really like this vest.

1226
00:38:26,770 --> 00:38:27,770
Do you remember

1227
00:38:28,470 --> 00:38:29,780
the vest Mom made for us

1228
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,210
when we got married?

1229
00:38:31,430 --> 00:38:33,460
How many years did we wear that vest?

1230
00:38:34,020 --> 00:38:35,660
Even now, that vest

1231
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:37,880
has no empty spaces where the cotton is.

1232
00:38:38,130 --> 00:38:39,460
Every stitch and thread

1233
00:38:39,470 --> 00:38:40,840
is filled with love.

1234
00:38:43,460 --> 00:38:45,530
I think it can last for another twenty years

1235
00:38:45,530 --> 00:38:47,000
without any problem.

1236
00:38:48,230 --> 00:38:50,360
You should flatter her in front of her.

1237
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:54,040
I'm not flattering her, you know?

1238
00:38:54,380 --> 00:38:55,350
If I really do,

1239
00:38:55,350 --> 00:38:56,290
I'll do it face-to-face.

1240
00:38:56,290 --> 00:38:58,150
What I'm saying is from the heart.

1241
00:38:58,550 --> 00:39:00,190
You see, many of our friends

1242
00:39:00,530 --> 00:39:01,990
no longer have their moms.

1243
00:39:02,130 --> 00:39:04,790
And we still have our mom making us little vests.

1244
00:39:04,940 --> 00:39:06,080
How lucky we are!

1245
00:39:07,340 --> 00:39:08,490
In this life,

1246
00:39:09,190 --> 00:39:10,590
as long as we have our mom,

1247
00:39:11,630 --> 00:39:13,640
there's no hardship.

1248
00:39:21,670 --> 00:39:22,400
Look.

1249
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:24,550
We also have a vest

1250
00:39:24,550 --> 00:39:26,060
made by Grandma.

1251
00:39:27,340 --> 00:39:28,900
Someone cares for us now,

1252
00:39:32,750 --> 00:39:35,030
so we won't feel cold anymore.

1253
00:40:50,120 --> 00:40:50,990
Zi.

1254
00:40:51,610 --> 00:40:52,340
Look.

1255
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:54,100
This is yellow.

1256
00:40:55,070 --> 00:40:56,120
Yellow.

1257
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:57,270
That one.

1258
00:40:57,510 --> 00:40:59,040
That's pink.

1259
00:41:00,830 --> 00:41:02,510
And that. See?

1260
00:41:03,070 --> 00:41:04,420
That's white.

1261
00:41:05,210 --> 00:41:07,120
Zi. What color is

1262
00:41:07,150 --> 00:41:08,480
your sister's clothes?

1263
00:41:10,230 --> 00:41:13,630
Sister.

1264
00:41:16,790 --> 00:41:18,300
Zi just called you Sister.

1265
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:21,080
Zi.

1266
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:22,720
Say it again.

1267
00:41:23,670 --> 00:41:24,780
Sister.

1268
00:41:29,430 --> 00:41:30,760
Sister.

1269
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,140
Zi, you're a good girl.

1270
00:41:41,130 --> 00:41:42,390
I'm leaving, Grandpa.

1271
00:41:43,940 --> 00:41:44,940
Let me see him out.

1272
00:41:53,420 --> 00:41:54,060
Grandpa,

1273
00:41:55,090 --> 00:41:56,350
take care of yourself.

1274
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:18,980
The New Year has passed,

1275
00:42:18,980 --> 00:42:20,580
the winter vacation is over,

1276
00:42:20,610 --> 00:42:22,520
and the people we miss have returned,

1277
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,920
but then they left again.

1278
00:42:24,340 --> 00:42:26,020
The year 1998 has come to us.

1279
00:42:26,470 --> 00:42:27,430
Grandma was eighteen

1280
00:42:27,430 --> 00:42:28,940
when she got together with Grandpa,

1281
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:30,880
and they've been fighting for a lifetime.

1282
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,010
Grandma always says

1283
00:42:32,140 --> 00:42:34,350
that the deputy factory manager liked her back then,

1284
00:42:34,350 --> 00:42:35,390
but she still impulsively married Grandpa

1285
00:42:35,390 --> 00:42:36,870
who had nothing.

1286
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:38,710
Grandpa didn't have any great skills,

1287
00:42:38,710 --> 00:42:39,920
but he was good to Grandma

1288
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:41,050
and good to the kids,

1289
00:42:41,370 --> 00:42:42,900
always cheerful every day.

1290
00:42:43,490 --> 00:42:44,620
Parents often think

1291
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:46,580
that as long as they love their children, that's enough.

1292
00:42:46,580 --> 00:42:48,020
But they don't realize

1293
00:42:48,050 --> 00:42:49,220
how important

1294
00:42:49,430 --> 00:42:50,620
a cheerful and laughter-filled home is

1295
00:42:50,620 --> 00:42:51,740
for children.

1296
00:42:52,590 --> 00:42:54,360
It determines whether you open the door each day

1297
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:55,730
to return to a safe harbor

1298
00:42:55,730 --> 00:42:56,930
or step into a cellar.

1299
00:42:57,170 --> 00:42:58,320
It also affects

1300
00:42:58,630 --> 00:42:59,410
whether, as you grow up,

1301
00:42:59,410 --> 00:43:01,340
you still remember and are willing

1302
00:43:01,650 --> 00:43:03,250
to open that door countless times.
